1
00:01:30,150 --> 00:01:34,920
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:37,720
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:44,870
Make way!

4
00:01:47,479 --> 00:01:48,940
Don't block the way. Move!

5
00:01:59,130 --> 00:02:02,870
A thorough inspection was conducted,
covering the process, installation,

6
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:04,310
materials, and quality.

7
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:05,770
Strictly...

8
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:08,910
Director, I told him
you were in a meeting,

9
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:09,430
but I couldn't stop him.

10
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:10,030
Piss off.

11
00:02:12,430 --> 00:02:14,240
That factory kid, Zhang Xiaoman,

12
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,000
was taken away by the City Bureau.

13
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,730
What do we do?

14
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:18,130
I heard from Security.

15
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,730
Isn't he the kid who got into a brawl

16
00:02:20,730 --> 00:02:21,960
in the family quarters last night?

17
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,120
How was it a brawl?

18
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:24,800
It wasn't a brawl.

19
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,470
Those hooligans were looking for trouble.

20
00:02:26,470 --> 00:02:27,840
Xiaoman was acting in self-defense.

21
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,590
H-How did it...

22
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:30,120
escalate into a brawl?

23
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,120
Mr. Ding, it's not up to us to decide.

24
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,800
You have to trust the government

25
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,670
and our laws.

26
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,970
If it was self-defense like you said,

27
00:02:40,970 --> 00:02:42,310
then Xiaoman will be fine.

28
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,450
No one will wrong him, right?

29
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:44,710
Well, that's how it is.

30
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:48,030
Let's put aside
whether he's wronged or not.

31
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:50,090
I feel so sorry for that kid, Xiaoman.

32
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,070
His dad is gone. No one looks after him.

33
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:52,870
You... just stop the meeting.

34
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:53,680
Go with me to the City Bureau

35
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:54,420
and bring him back first.

36
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:54,950
Let's go.

37
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,490
Move it, won't you?

38
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:57,430
No, Mr. Ding.

39
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:00,080
Our entire factory has
ten to twenty thousand employees.

40
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,610
Fights happen every month.

41
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,520
If I have to go pick them up every time,

42
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:05,250
how will the factory function?

43
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:09,400
Besides, I'm not in charge of
the City Bureau's leaders.

44
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:10,910
My hands are tied.

45
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:13,480
If there's nothing else, please leave.

46
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,540
We're in a meeting.

47
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:16,310
Mr. Ding, the leadership team
is in a meeting.

48
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:17,000
I'll whack you.

49
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,730
-Sit down.
-What are you doing?

50
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:19,980
Ding Guoqiang.

51
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:22,110
You still want to fight?

52
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,020
Come, hit me!

53
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,340
The whole factory knows it anyway.

54
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,870
You slapped me once before.

55
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,829
It doesn't matter if you
hit me with a rolling pin now.

56
00:03:30,829 --> 00:03:31,640
Come on, do it!

57
00:03:38,270 --> 00:03:38,960
I was wrong.

58
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:41,120
I shouldn't have

59
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,380
slapped you back then.

60
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:43,870
How about this?

61
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:44,770
You slap me twice.

62
00:03:44,770 --> 00:03:45,560
Get even.

63
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:47,430
How about I kowtow to you?

64
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:48,120
M-Mr. Ding!

65
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,320
W-What are you doing?

66
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:50,870
I'll get on my knees. Is that okay?

67
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:51,930
What are you doing?

68
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,680
What happened between us

69
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,520
is in the past.

70
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:58,100
If I really had a grudge against you,

71
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:00,100
I wouldn't have waited until today.

72
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:04,100
How about this? Let's tell them

73
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:05,800
how pitiful Xiaoman is.

74
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:08,220
He has no family to rely on.

75
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:09,380
He's taking the college entrance exam.

76
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:11,110
This could ruin his whole life.

77
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:13,100
Mr. Ding.

78
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,120
In the past,

79
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:18,079
Security would handle fights
within the factory.

80
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,410
If so, I could have a say.

81
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,339
But things are different now.

82
00:04:22,290 --> 00:04:23,320
It's been escalated to the City Bureau.

83
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,550
It won't make a difference even if I go.

84
00:04:24,550 --> 00:04:25,630
How would it be of no use?

85
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:26,720
Director, everyone knows

86
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,070
you're a prefecture-level cadre
who transferred over.

87
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:30,430
Even the vice mayor has to respect you.

88
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:31,040
Even the Bureau Chief

89
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,170
has to listen to you.

90
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:33,190
We're not asking for much.

91
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,270
Let's just clear this up

92
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:35,040
and get the kid out.

93
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,270
Okay, Mr. Ding.

94
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:37,360
I'll go with you.

95
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:37,870
I'll go with you.

96
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:38,560
Let's go.

97
00:04:38,580 --> 00:04:39,480
Okay.

98
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:40,870
The rolling pin.

99
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:22,750
What's wrong?

100
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,360
Yan Xiaodan, get back here!

101
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:30,920
Yan Xiaodan, get back here!

102
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,270
Officer,

103
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,250
I understand we have legal procedures and

104
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:36,970
organizational discipline.

105
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,720
But Zhang Xiaoman is
a child of our factory.

106
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,000
As the factory director,

107
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,040
I must take responsibility for him.

108
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:45,180
Of course,

109
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:48,870
it was definitely wrong for
Zhang Xiaoman to hurt someone.

110
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:49,870
After we get back,

111
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:51,750
we will discipline him.

112
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:53,680
However,

113
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,950
I do also understand

114
00:05:55,970 --> 00:05:57,300
what exactly happened.

115
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,430
It was mainly because Feng Xiaobo

116
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:00,490
retaliated first.

117
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:02,870
So I hope the police

118
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:05,020
will investigate thoroughly

119
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:06,480
and handle this properly.

120
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,220
Mr. Ding?

121
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,720
Allow me to say a few words.

122
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:15,520
Go ahead.

123
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,120
Xiaoman was the one being bullied.

124
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,830
Why couldn't he fight back?

125
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,270
Look.

126
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,100
You're wearing a police uniform.

127
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,580
And I used to wear a military uniform.

128
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,020
To be straightfoward,

129
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:30,190
it was just a fight between teens.

130
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:31,040
Aren't some scrapes

131
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,600
and a little bleeding normal?

132
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,070
So what?

133
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:34,730
Is it necessary to lock him up?

134
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:36,510
Besides, before you became a cop,

135
00:06:36,510 --> 00:06:38,440
have you never gotten into a fight?

136
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,909
What I mean is,

137
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:43,120
I-I'll take Xiaoman back,

138
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:44,270
and I'll discipline him at home.

139
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,480
I'm more effective than the police.

140
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,210
Mr. Ding, let me put it this way.

141
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:50,570
This is no longer just
a fight between children.

142
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:51,270
Isn't it just—

143
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:54,120
Feng Xiaobo is being resuscitated
in the hospital.

144
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,470
Zhang Xiaoman's actions

145
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:57,460
have caused serious consequences.

146
00:06:57,460 --> 00:06:58,870
If you are asking me to release him now,

147
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:00,120
I definitely can't.

148
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,630
Look, this is just...

149
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:06,870
Say something.

150
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:07,820
You see... this kid...

151
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:09,240
Let's not talk about the
college entrance exam.

152
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,270
If this gets on his record,

153
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,450
it'll ruin his whole life.

154
00:07:11,450 --> 00:07:12,690
What are you doing?

155
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,720
Can you keep it down?

156
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,270
So I can't speak?

157
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,670
This is a police station.

158
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,400
Officer Leng, look.

159
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,520
Officer Leng.

160
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,510
If you find it difficult

161
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,720
to make a decision

162
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,480
right now,

163
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:28,210
I can meet your superiors.

164
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,920
I know Chief Wang quite well.

165
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,040
I can explain the situation

166
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,110
to him,

167
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:33,870
and we can discuss

168
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
a solution together. Okay?

169
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:37,330
Director Meng.

170
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,720
To be honest,

171
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:42,120
no one can help you now.

172
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,680
Zhang Xiaoman has caused

173
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,210
substantial harm to Feng Xiaobo.

174
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:47,330
And we have already

175
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:49,280
initiated judicial proceedings.

176
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:51,720
But please trust the police

177
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,870
and the law

178
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:54,720
to give him a fair outcome.

179
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:55,920
Okay?

180
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,770
Please go back for now.

181
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,000
So what now?

182
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:04,070
Xiaoman has lost his father.

183
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:05,040
How can I just stand by and watch?

184
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,970
Keep it down. The child is outside.

185
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,480
All's good. I'm handling it.

186
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:30,640
Chief Engineer Yan.

187
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:33,440
Yan.

188
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:36,200
Tell us about it.

189
00:08:39,809 --> 00:08:40,669
Director Meng.

190
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:42,080
Captain Leng.

191
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,210
Chief Engineer Yan.

192
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,330
If it's convenient,

193
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:47,720
I'll talk to you alone.

194
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:48,320
What is this?

195
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,510
Why the private talk?

196
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:51,170
Why can't you say it to my face?

197
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,910
The kid is about to go to jail.

198
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,270
What are you dawdling about?

199
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:54,870
Mr. Ding,

200
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:56,910
watch your attitude.

201
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,510
Stop picking on me, I'm telling you!

202
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,310
What? You going to detain me too?

203
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:01,720
What is wrong with you people?

204
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,080
Can't you calm down?

205
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,270
Watch your attitude, will you?

206
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:06,080
What kind of attitude am I having?

207
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,080
If your Meng Ge had been arrested,

208
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,270
would you be watching your attitude?

209
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,930
W-Who could stand all of this?

210
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,880
Talking about that is useless.

211
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:21,750
Come. Sit down.

212
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:24,090
Sit down.

213
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:29,840
Why are you here?

214
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:31,220
You have no business here. Go home.

215
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:32,840
What do you mean it's none of my business?

216
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:35,240
If it weren't for me,
would Xiaoman be here?

217
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,860
This is everything that
happened that night.

218
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:39,980
I wrote it all down.

219
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,720
I even put my fingerprint on it.

220
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,550
I can testify.

221
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:43,720
Xiaoman was just defending me.

222
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,240
This has nothing to do with Xiaodan.

223
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,240
I can testify!

224
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:47,510
Chen, take him outside.

225
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:48,240
Officer Leng!

226
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:48,910
Go outside first.

227
00:09:48,910 --> 00:09:49,790
I can testify.

228
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,290
Chief Engineer Yan.

229
00:10:02,950 --> 00:10:04,670
Everyone, please step outside
for a moment.

230
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:05,120
Okay.

231
00:10:06,270 --> 00:10:06,990
You too.

232
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:09,670
Let's go.

233
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,510
Thanks for the trouble.

234
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:12,630
Why are you coming out again?

235
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,550
What are you doing?

236
00:10:13,550 --> 00:10:15,040
What is going on here?

237
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,030
Chen.

238
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:28,240
Bring Zhang Xiaoman in.

239
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:28,800
Yes, Sir.

240
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:32,830
Come in.

241
00:10:38,130 --> 00:10:38,730
Go inside.

242
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,580
Chen, step out and close the door.

243
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:42,400
Yes, Sir.

244
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:46,910
Zhang Xiaoman.

245
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:51,080
When you gave your statement,

246
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,080
why didn't you mention that

247
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,270
it was Feng Xiaobo who was
attempting to assault

248
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:56,080
Yan Xiaodan?

249
00:10:56,910 --> 00:10:57,720
Officer Leng,

250
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,300
I started it.

251
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,630
Xiaodan had already run away.

252
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:01,910
This has nothing to do with her.

253
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,510
Zhang Xiaoman, let me remind you.

254
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:05,710
This determines the nature of the case.

255
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,160
Think clearly before you speak.

256
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:17,800
Officer Leng.

257
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:21,750
Can I...

258
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:24,600
ask you for a favor?

259
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:25,840
Go ahead.

260
00:11:30,350 --> 00:11:33,080
Xiaodan is taking the
college entrance exam soon.

261
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,810
It's less than two months away.

262
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:37,550
Can we keep this

263
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,400
from affecting her exam?

264
00:11:45,510 --> 00:11:46,270
Understood.

265
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:51,120
It's also the police's duty to protect
the involved parties.

266
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:52,890
How about this?

267
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,080
Think it over carefully.

268
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:59,510
Tell me when you've thought it through,

269
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:01,400
and whether you want

270
00:12:02,470 --> 00:12:03,870
to add to your statement.

271
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:07,050
Also, let me remind you of one thing.

272
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:12,120
Don't let Yan Xiaodan down

273
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,980
after all that she's done for you.

274
00:12:20,870 --> 00:12:21,720
You...

275
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,010
You just won't listen.

276
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,240
I told you long ago

277
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,240
that if something like this happens,

278
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,120
just leave it to your family.

279
00:12:29,930 --> 00:12:31,870
Xiaodan, are you involved in this too?

280
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:32,800
Why are you here?

281
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,850
Enough. Come home with me.

282
00:12:37,670 --> 00:12:38,130
I won't.

283
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,370
Let's go.

284
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:41,840
Goodness.

285
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:43,440
Let me see.

286
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,080
How did this happen?

287
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:49,120
You and Mom shouldn't have locked me in.

288
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,270
What a beast. Locking up your own child?

289
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,190
Shut up.

290
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,790
Dad, don't you think you're too selfish?

291
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,450
I know you don't like Xiaoman.

292
00:12:56,790 --> 00:12:58,720
But compared to someone's life and future,

293
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,720
is your reputation that important?

294
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:03,960
You're still young.
There are things you don't understand.

295
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:06,490
I'll explain it to you slowly
when we get home.

296
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:09,880
Is Xiaoman alright now?

297
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:11,940
Xiaodan, thank you.

298
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,140
The information you provided

299
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:16,080
was very helpful to Zhang Xiaoman.

300
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,720
I see Chief Engineer Yan is here too.

301
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,000
As Xiaodan's father,

302
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:22,270
we need you to

303
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:25,440
accompany her to give a statement
in a moment.

304
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,720
Okay, I'll cooperate.

305
00:13:27,230 --> 00:13:28,560
So long as it's helpful.

306
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:29,690
Thank you, Xiaodan.

307
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:32,010
Based on what we know so far,

308
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,440
although Zhang Xiaoman injured someone,

309
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,550
it was triggered by Feng Xiaobo's

310
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:39,270
retaliation against him.

311
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,030
Also, we just received a call.

312
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,000
Feng Xiaobo is out of critical condition.

313
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,270
That also helps with
the eventual classification

314
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:46,330
of Xiaoman's case.

315
00:13:46,580 --> 00:13:47,390
That's great.

316
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,650
Thank goodness.

317
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,120
Bad guys live long lives.

318
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:51,840
Why don't you uncuff him?

319
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:52,720
Why is he still in handcuffs?

320
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,780
Look at things now.

321
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,720
Once the details have been ascertained,

322
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,080
we will definitely take them off.

323
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:57,720
Mr. Ding.

324
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,550
In a moment,

325
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,840
we need to take another statement
from Xiaoman.

326
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,390
Okay.

327
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:03,450
Please come along.

328
00:14:03,470 --> 00:14:04,510
No, it's no trouble at all.

329
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,270
I-I'm fine.

330
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,270
I won't do anything else today.

331
00:14:06,270 --> 00:14:07,080
I'll just stay with him.

332
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:07,870
Let alone taking a statement,

333
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:09,440
I'd even stay locked up with him
for two days.

334
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,780
Okay, thanks. Let's go.

335
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,760
No, I thank you.

336
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,080
Leng, I'm sorry.

337
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,870
My attitude earlier was out of line.

338
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:16,150
You're just doing your job by the book.

339
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:17,950
You're bound to get a promotion.

340
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,000
Xiaodan,

341
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,900
did you see the fireworks?

342
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:44,510
Yes, I saw them.

343
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,080
Just pack two pieces.

344
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,080
We don't know if it can be delivered.

345
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,510
I told you, two pieces are enough.

346
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:05,570
We don't even know if we can send it in.

347
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:08,750
This kid

348
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:11,040
has no priorities.

349
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:13,660
By now,

350
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:16,480
the college entrance exam
is just around the corner.

351
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,080
Xiaoman!

352
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:20,170
Uncle Ding.

353
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,910
W-Where is Xiaoman?

354
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:23,720
Why didn't he come back?

355
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,180
Wait, Auntie, why are you packing?

356
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,910
No, don't scare me.

357
00:15:27,910 --> 00:15:29,770
Is Xiaoman not coming out, Uncle?

358
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:30,490
Is it—

359
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:32,270
Enough. They're investigating.

360
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,510
What is there to investigate?

361
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:35,270
Xiaodan went to testify, didn't she?

362
00:15:35,270 --> 00:15:37,630
What happened, Mr. Ding?
How long is his sentence?

363
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:38,630
What sentence?

364
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:40,090
Stop making things worse.

365
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:41,320
Go home.

366
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,260
Don't tell anyone.
This must not get out.

367
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,870
Uncle, let us go with you.

368
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:48,510
Just stay here.

369
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,870
I haven't even packed the clothes yet.

370
00:15:49,870 --> 00:15:51,270
Don't make things worse!

371
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,480
What's going on, Auntie?

372
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,750
Will Xiaoman get out?

373
00:15:56,390 --> 00:15:58,240
I'm scared. Don't...

374
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:00,520
Don't worry.

375
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:02,870
Our child is a good kid.

376
00:16:03,270 --> 00:16:04,080
It'll be okay.

377
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:05,870
Everything will be okay.

378
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:09,010
There's no way a child like Xiaoman
not get released.

379
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:22,360
Everyone, put down your pens for a moment.

380
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:26,010
I want to talk about
the college application forms.

381
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:29,270
Everyone, based on your mock exam results,

382
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:31,070
fill out this application form.

383
00:16:31,630 --> 00:16:32,720
Between your first choice,

384
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,580
second choice,

385
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:34,550
and third choice,

386
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:36,750
you should leave a larger score margin.

387
00:16:36,910 --> 00:16:39,310
You can refer to
last year's cutoff scores.

388
00:16:40,510 --> 00:16:41,910
The most important thing

389
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:44,790
is that you must think clearly about

390
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,710
whether you agree to being reassigned.

391
00:16:47,930 --> 00:16:50,120
When filling out this application form,

392
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,180
you must think it through carefully.

393
00:16:53,630 --> 00:16:54,890
If you fill it out well,

394
00:16:55,030 --> 00:16:57,270
you can get in just by meeting the cutoff.

395
00:16:57,270 --> 00:16:58,800
If you don't fill it out well

396
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,260
and refuse reassignment,

397
00:17:00,870 --> 00:17:03,960
it may result in no university
accepting you.

398
00:17:04,970 --> 00:17:05,800
You'll have to

399
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:10,920
enter the workforce or retake the exam.

400
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,630
So, we suggest that you all

401
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,310
agree to the reassignment.

402
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,680
This is a matter that will affect
the rest of your lives.

403
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,790
Is that clear?

404
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,480
Yes.

405
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:30,180
If you have any questions,

406
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:33,920
you can come and talk to me.

407
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,280
However,

408
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:38,890
I can only give you objective advice.

409
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,110
At this moment,

410
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,720
and also speaking for myself,

411
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,070
I hope you all

412
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:53,880
get into your dream universities.

413
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,550
Thank you, Teacher.

414
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:57,920
Go for it!

415
00:17:59,590 --> 00:18:00,790
Let's do this, everyone!

416
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,110
Go for it!

417
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:02,920
All the best!

418
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:08,290
Alright, everyone, focus on your revision.

419
00:18:23,950 --> 00:18:25,840
He, let's switch seats.

420
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:26,900
Okay.

421
00:18:31,580 --> 00:18:33,380
Where are you planning to apply?

422
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,140
My dad has already decided

423
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,010
where I will be applying to.

424
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,590
March in unison!

425
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:01,490
[According to Article 234 of the Second Edition of the Criminal Law
of the People's Republic of China (1997),]

426
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,830
[Zhang Xiaoman was found guilty of grievous hurt,
and was sentenced to six months of detention.]

427
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:07,830
[Additionally, pursuant to Article 17, Paragraph 3 of the Criminal Law
of the People's Republic of China, Zhang Xiaoman was over 16 but under 18 years of age.]

428
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:11,160
[In accordance with the law, a lighter or reduced punishment shall be imposed. The defendant is sentenced to a juvenile detention center.
The term of imprisonment shall be calculated from the date of commencement of the sentence.]

429
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:21,680
Done.

430
00:19:22,270 --> 00:19:24,470
Done? What about the other choices?

431
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:28,330
I only want to go to Tongzhou University.

432
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,510
No, think it through.

433
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,310
If you don't get in,

434
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:34,310
you'll have to repeat a year.

435
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:37,570
I wanted to testify at the police station,

436
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:38,900
but you wouldn't let me.

437
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,480
And now, the whole family
has to move to Shanghai.

438
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,740
We do whatever you say.

439
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,790
When do I ever

440
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:43,680
get to decide?

441
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:46,920
So this is where you were going with this.

442
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:47,830
Let me tell you,

443
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:51,350
I don't think
it's worth risking your own life

444
00:19:51,710 --> 00:19:53,240
just to spite your parents.

445
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:54,310
I'm not doing that.

446
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:55,480
I just want to go to Tongzhou University.

447
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,920
You can fill in the rest for me.

448
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:57,550
Whatever works, right?

449
00:19:57,550 --> 00:19:58,790
You just want me to go to Shanghai,
don't you?

450
00:19:58,790 --> 00:20:00,030
Whether I go to a technical school
or another college,

451
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:01,070
it doesn't matter to me.

452
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:02,400
If it doesn't matter,
then don't take the exam.

453
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,030
That's even better.

454
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:03,750
Why go to college?

455
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:05,110
Great. I'll just stay here then.

456
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,770
You can stay here by yourself.

457
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:08,200
I can. Why can't I?

458
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:08,750
It doesn't matter.

459
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,710
We'll all leave and leave her alone.

460
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,510
Let her stay here by herself.

461
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:13,070
Right?

462
00:20:13,070 --> 00:20:14,920
Alright, stop talking.

463
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:19,470
Sweetie, what's wrong?

464
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:21,810
Mom, stop trying to be the peacemaker.

465
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:25,960
I know you grew up here.

466
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,640
You can't bear to leave, right?

467
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:29,710
But you also have to understand
your father.

468
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:31,140
He has his own hometown.

469
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:32,970
He's been away for so many years.

470
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:34,350
Alright.

471
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,510
And you said you weren't being
a peacemaker.

472
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,830
Your father is indeed a bit overbearing.

473
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,660
But he's not wrong.

474
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:45,920
You can't take your anger out
on your future.

475
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,270
Do you understand?

476
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:48,070
I'm not.

477
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:50,870
I'm confident I can get into
Tongzhou University.

478
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,520
Then tell him that.

479
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,440
Talk to your father nicely.

480
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,300
Look how anxious you've made him.

481
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:58,440
Talk to him nicely, okay, sweetie?

482
00:20:59,310 --> 00:21:00,920
I just want him to be anxious.

483
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,510
Your father is getting old.

484
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:05,310
He can't win against you, you know?

485
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:06,850
I'll go cut some fruit for you.

486
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:07,850
Study hard.

487
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,140
Be good.

488
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,770
Mr. Gu, stop pulling.

489
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:15,270
Look, it's falling apart.

490
00:21:15,270 --> 00:21:16,370
Mr. Gu, please.

491
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:16,920
No, it won't.

492
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,170
Mr. Gu, don't buy them.

493
00:21:18,170 --> 00:21:18,790
I'll give you two for free.

494
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:19,730
You don't have to buy it.

495
00:21:19,730 --> 00:21:20,310
I'll give you two.

496
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:20,790
I can't accept that.

497
00:21:20,790 --> 00:21:21,680
Just take them.

498
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:22,920
Then I won't buy any.

499
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:23,680
Fine, forget it.

500
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,920
Mr. Gu, grocery shopping?

501
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:27,310
Xia Lei's mom?

502
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,510
That's a lot of groceries.

503
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:31,370
I bought a carp to nourish Xia Lei.

504
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,070
Yes, yes.

505
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,030
At this critical moment,

506
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:35,640
he does need extra nourishment.

507
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,270
I've been meaning to thank you.

508
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:38,160
Xia Lei

509
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:39,770
often mentions you at home.

510
00:21:39,790 --> 00:21:42,480
He says you are a responsible and
good teacher.

511
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:44,070
His math grades are really...

512
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,200
thanks to your hard work and guidance.

513
00:21:46,460 --> 00:21:47,720
It's our duty.

514
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,510
As teachers,

515
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:52,640
we are happiest when we meet

516
00:21:52,640 --> 00:21:53,700
students like Xia Lei,

517
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:54,680
and parents like you

518
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,120
who value education.

519
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:58,400
Recently,

520
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,330
isn't it time for the kids to fill out
their college applications?

521
00:22:01,330 --> 00:22:02,920
We are a working-class family,

522
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,180
so we don't have much experience.

523
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:05,270
I was also hoping to

524
00:22:05,270 --> 00:22:06,440
ask you for some advice

525
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,310
and guidance.

526
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:12,640
The child's own ideas and wishes
are very important.

527
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:15,000
He doesn't have any ideas.

528
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:17,960
He's putting all his energy into
studying right now.

529
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,240
Regarding the application,

530
00:22:21,510 --> 00:22:23,040
first, consider the major,

531
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,030
and second, consider the city.

532
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:26,070
As for the city,

533
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,540
go to Shanghai.

534
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:32,070
Shanghai is developing well right now.

535
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:33,160
Shanghai?

536
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,270
Shanghai...

537
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,720
Shanghai is a bit far, isn't it?

538
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,400
Well, I was thinking maybe

539
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:41,800
I should let him try for
maybe Tsinghua or Peking University.

540
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:43,400
I recommend Shanghai

541
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:47,850
because I think the growth potential
generated by Pudong's development

542
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:50,510
won't be exhausted within
the next twenty to thirty years.

543
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:52,240
If Xia Lei goes to college in Shanghai,

544
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:55,240
he'll be just in time to
catch this great opportunity.

545
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:56,440
Well,

546
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,160
thank you, Mr. Gu.

547
00:22:58,830 --> 00:22:59,920
We will definitely go back

548
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,450
and consider it seriously.

549
00:23:03,030 --> 00:23:05,290
You didn't manage to buy any vegetables.

550
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:08,070
Take these potatoes of mine.

551
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,600
I handpicked these potatoes one by one,

552
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:11,680
all of them carefully selected.

553
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:12,510
In the whole market,

554
00:23:12,510 --> 00:23:14,310
you won't find better potatoes.

555
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:15,350
You're too kind.

556
00:23:15,350 --> 00:23:16,480
I can't accept this.

557
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:19,020
I also hope Xia Lei does well too.

558
00:23:19,270 --> 00:23:19,640
No, no.

559
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:22,310
How about you come over
for dinner someday?

560
00:23:22,310 --> 00:23:23,680
Xia Lei's dad is a good cook.

561
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,020
He'll prepare a feast for you.

562
00:23:25,020 --> 00:23:25,920
Take this.

563
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:26,510
Take it.

564
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,540
How about this, I'll take one.

565
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:29,170
One?

566
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:30,460
One is enough.

567
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:32,070
Thank you.

568
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:35,480
I've long heard that your husband
is a great cook.

569
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:37,680
When Xia Lei gets into a university
in Shanghai,

570
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:38,580
you can treat me then.

571
00:23:38,580 --> 00:23:39,550
Of course.

572
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:40,370
Definitely.

573
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:41,710
Okay.

574
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:44,680
Mr. Gu, I'm heading home.

575
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,540
I live this way.

576
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:48,770
You aren't going this way?

577
00:23:49,270 --> 00:23:50,270
Thank you, Mr. Gu.

578
00:23:50,540 --> 00:23:51,250
See you.

579
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:54,590
Plus

580
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,200
one over cosine C

581
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,730
equals negative twice the square root
of two.

582
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:00,720
So...

583
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:01,720
You're wrong.

584
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,960
That's not what our teacher said
this morning.

585
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:04,560
It should be written up here.

586
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,440
Let me simplify this equation then.

587
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:13,480
Cosine A plus cosine C equals

588
00:24:13,510 --> 00:24:15,920
equals negative twice the square root
of two.

589
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,200
Cosine A... cosine C...

590
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:28,340
Xiaodan, what's up?

591
00:24:29,110 --> 00:24:30,590
I'm going to visit Xiaoman this afternoon.

592
00:24:30,590 --> 00:24:31,650
Do you want to come?

593
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:32,640
This afternoon?

594
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:35,120
Isn't there a cram session this afternoon?

595
00:24:37,550 --> 00:24:39,410
Did Ms. Tong give you permission?

596
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:41,830
I'm skipping class.

597
00:24:46,330 --> 00:24:47,960
Why don't we go this weekend?

598
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:50,120
I should probably be able to

599
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,120
sneak out then.

600
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:55,790
Whenever I think of Xiaoman
in juvenile detention,

601
00:24:55,790 --> 00:24:57,850
I just can't focus on studying at all.

602
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:02,960
Don't blame yourself for
what happened to Xiaoman.

603
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,030
It has nothing to do with you.

604
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:12,550
It's all that bastard Feng Xiaobo's fault.

605
00:25:12,550 --> 00:25:14,350
Exactly. It's all that bastard's fault.

606
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:15,550
I'm telling you, if I had been there,

607
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:17,150
I would have stabbed him too.

608
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:18,440
Seriously. I'm not bluffing.

609
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,200
I really would have stabbed him.

610
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,730
I-I definitely would have.

611
00:25:22,110 --> 00:25:22,960
I'm just worried that Xiaoman

612
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:25,820
will get bullied in the
juvenile detention center.

613
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:28,840
He wouldn't be bullied,

614
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:31,410
and he wouldn't bully others either.

615
00:25:38,590 --> 00:25:39,450
Zhang Xiaoman!

616
00:25:39,590 --> 00:25:40,030
Here!

617
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:40,890
Zhang Xiaoman!

618
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,430
Come! You have a visitor!

619
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:53,680
Come in.

620
00:25:54,550 --> 00:25:55,350
Number seven.

621
00:26:07,870 --> 00:26:08,730
Can you hear me?

622
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:09,440
Mr. Ding.

623
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,830
Xia Lei and Xiaodan didn't come?

624
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:12,510
What's with that look?

625
00:26:12,510 --> 00:26:14,310
Did I make a mistake coming here?

626
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:15,640
You only care about them.

627
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,000
What? Am I not welcomed?

628
00:26:17,020 --> 00:26:17,870
No, no.

629
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:19,570
I just miss them.

630
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:25,030
It's only a month left to
the college entrance exams.

631
00:26:25,030 --> 00:26:27,440
Those two are suffering
more than you right now.

632
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:30,350
If you asked them to switch places
with you now,

633
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,440
they'd be in here in a heartbeat.

634
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,260
But their parents held them back.

635
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,240
Well, I'm definitely...

636
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:40,290
going to miss the exams.

637
00:26:41,710 --> 00:26:44,200
You're thinking too far ahead.
Don't lose heart.

638
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,350
You're in juvenile detention.

639
00:26:45,350 --> 00:26:47,480
If you behave, there's still a chance.

640
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,500
About your dad... don't blame me.

641
00:26:54,730 --> 00:26:56,140
I wanted to wait until you grew up,

642
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:58,600
until after your exams
to tell you properly.

643
00:27:08,580 --> 00:27:10,350
This is... my friend.

644
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:11,200
What did I do wrong

645
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,730
to have to apologize to her?

646
00:27:15,180 --> 00:27:17,010
Here, one more!

647
00:27:28,550 --> 00:27:31,440
I know everything now.
You were doing this for my own good,

648
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,030
therefore keeping me in the dark.

649
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:35,630
It's all right, Uncle.
He's had a hard life too.

650
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:40,550
Zhang Xiaoman, let me ask you.

651
00:27:40,550 --> 00:27:42,160
You little brats,

652
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:44,220
have you been talking behind my back?

653
00:27:45,790 --> 00:27:46,510
No.

654
00:27:47,350 --> 00:27:48,200
Really?

655
00:27:48,590 --> 00:27:49,160
No.

656
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:49,860
No?

657
00:27:50,350 --> 00:27:52,510
I know everything by now,
and you still say no?

658
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:54,170
Is it divided into things like

659
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,440
Northern and Southern Shaolin?

660
00:27:56,790 --> 00:27:57,790
And then you say I got hit

661
00:27:57,790 --> 00:27:59,030
by a nun's palm strike.

662
00:27:59,030 --> 00:28:00,030
That kungfu move?

663
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:02,750
What was the name of that move again?

664
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,550
Eagle Claw Lineage-Ending Palm?

665
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:07,350
Look at the name you came up with.

666
00:28:10,550 --> 00:28:11,590
I didn't name it.

667
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,200
The guys across from me did.

668
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,460
They aren't on my side.

669
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:17,350
You're too honest, kid.
I tricked it out of you just like that.

670
00:28:17,350 --> 00:28:19,350
Just watch me go back and beat him up.

671
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:23,750
Eagle Claw Lineage-Ending Palm.

672
00:28:23,750 --> 00:28:25,550
I didn't plan for the line to end with me.

673
00:28:25,550 --> 00:28:26,750
But I did get injured.

674
00:28:26,910 --> 00:28:29,590
Actually, after I returned from my injury,

675
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,030
I didn't think I could still

676
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:33,310
find someone to marry.

677
00:28:33,790 --> 00:28:34,790
So I went to the factory.

678
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:36,030
Then one winter,

679
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:38,030
I saw your aunt

680
00:28:38,030 --> 00:28:39,640
fishing by an ice hole.

681
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,180
I said to myself,
"This woman is something else!

682
00:28:41,180 --> 00:28:43,050
She's so amazing!

683
00:28:43,070 --> 00:28:44,960
So wild and tough!"

684
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,750
I was just thinking about that,

685
00:28:46,750 --> 00:28:48,440
and the very next year,

686
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,300
we got married.

687
00:28:49,550 --> 00:28:51,030
So, with people,

688
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:56,030
you never know if you're stepping into
dog crap or good luck.

689
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:57,490
Everything's uncertain.

690
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,640
Uncle Ding, I...

691
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:03,930
I understand.
You don't need to try to comfort me.

692
00:29:05,420 --> 00:29:07,620
I was too impatient this time.

693
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,140
I didn't know when to stop.

694
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:12,770
I'll reform myself in here.

695
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:14,280
I'll be fine.

696
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,750
As long as you're good, Xiaoman.

697
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,900
As long as you behave in there,

698
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:21,570
there's still hope for us
when you get out.

699
00:29:23,310 --> 00:29:25,350
You call this studying?

700
00:29:30,750 --> 00:29:32,830
Dad, please take me to see Xiaoman.

701
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:35,590
You can't. Didn't I tell you?

702
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:40,180
The juvenile detention center only allows
visits Monday through Thursday.

703
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:41,980
I can take time off.

704
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:44,420
Take time off for what?

705
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:46,250
How many times have we talked about this?

706
00:29:46,250 --> 00:29:47,750
The college entrance exam
is just days away.

707
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:49,410
You can't get distracted now.

708
00:29:49,550 --> 00:29:50,920
Just let me see him once.

709
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:53,160
After all, he's in there because of me.

710
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:54,390
Going to see him now will

711
00:29:54,390 --> 00:29:56,050
definitely affect your mood.

712
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:58,290
Do you think Xiaoman wants to see that?

713
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:00,260
I'm back.

714
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:03,480
No, he wouldn't.

715
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,070
Here, have some oranges.

716
00:30:05,950 --> 00:30:07,190
But by not seeing him

717
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:09,500
and thinking about him being in there...

718
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:11,000
it affects my mood even more.

719
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:12,270
I feel even worse.

720
00:30:12,270 --> 00:30:13,510
Let's not feel bad, okay?

721
00:30:13,510 --> 00:30:14,370
How about this?

722
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:16,920
I will take you to see him as soon as
the college entrance exam is over.

723
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:17,480
Really?

724
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,000
It's a deal.

725
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:24,680
It's a deal.

726
00:30:25,110 --> 00:30:26,240
I'll go revise then.

727
00:30:26,850 --> 00:30:27,440
Yan.

728
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,920
Eat some fruit if you get thirsty, okay?

729
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:31,890
All the best.

730
00:30:32,150 --> 00:30:32,750
Yan.

731
00:30:37,350 --> 00:30:39,440
How could you agree to that?

732
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:41,350
I know what I'm doing.

733
00:30:41,550 --> 00:30:42,790
You agree first,

734
00:30:43,020 --> 00:30:44,350
and she'll just... you know?

735
00:30:44,350 --> 00:30:45,510
Once she... you know,

736
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:47,370
won't everything be... you know?

737
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:49,160
What do you exactly mean?

738
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,420
What do you think it is?

739
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:51,900
You don't understand.

740
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:52,750
Report!

741
00:30:53,350 --> 00:30:54,160
What is it?

742
00:30:55,310 --> 00:30:57,680
Officer, there's a scarlet sage
over there.

743
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:58,340
Pull it out.

744
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:01,960
Aren't we here to pull weeds?

745
00:31:02,030 --> 00:31:03,160
That's a flower.

746
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,920
So you're just gonna leave it there?

747
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:12,750
Sir!

748
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:13,750
Speak.

749
00:31:14,310 --> 00:31:16,920
Can I dig it up and keep it?

750
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:18,440
Sure.

751
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:19,700
Permission granted.

752
00:31:19,700 --> 00:31:21,110
Go find a tool.

753
00:31:21,130 --> 00:31:22,260
Thank you, Officer.

754
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:38,550
Yan.

755
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:40,270
Yan.

756
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:42,160
This kid has changed.

757
00:32:44,270 --> 00:32:46,000
She's staying up late to study.

758
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,200
Still studying?

759
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:51,810
That's a good thing.

760
00:32:53,490 --> 00:32:55,160
Make her a late-night snack later.

761
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:57,110
We need to keep up with her nutrition.

762
00:32:57,110 --> 00:32:58,570
I already brought her milk

763
00:32:58,710 --> 00:32:59,790
and apples.

764
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:00,790
Don't worry.

765
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:03,350
On her calendar,

766
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:06,350
besides marking
the college entrance exam dates,

767
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:07,720
there's another marked date.

768
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,000
October 18.

769
00:33:09,310 --> 00:33:10,310
What day is that?

770
00:33:10,350 --> 00:33:12,000
The day Xiaoman is released.

771
00:33:13,510 --> 00:33:16,170
Will she come back from Shanghai
to see him then?

772
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:18,310
Impossible.

773
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:20,520
Just rest assured.

774
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:21,580
Think about it.

775
00:33:22,030 --> 00:33:23,750
Once she gets to a new school,

776
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:27,360
it's a new environment with
new classmates and teachers.

777
00:33:27,750 --> 00:33:29,150
At Tongzhou University,

778
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:32,240
there will be plenty of outstanding boys.

779
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:33,970
Talented ones, handsome ones.

780
00:33:34,270 --> 00:33:34,750
Right?

781
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:38,830
Over time,
she'll drift apart from Xiaoman.

782
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:40,220
They'll grow distant.

783
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,720
I hope so.

784
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,590
Don't worry.

785
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,920
Think back to when we were in college.

786
00:33:46,070 --> 00:33:48,070
What did you see in me as your senior?

787
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,750
Was it talent or looks?

788
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,790
I liked everything about him.

789
00:33:56,850 --> 00:33:58,310
Do you think she can get in?

790
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:00,580
No problem.

791
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:02,550
Really?

792
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:14,430
[Countdown to college entrance exam:
28 days]

793
00:35:16,610 --> 00:35:19,860
Come, let's solve question 21.

794
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:22,480
Let's look at triangle ABC.

795
00:35:22,590 --> 00:35:23,510
What is given?

796
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:31,550
Angle A plus Angle C equals...

797
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:36,880
...two times of Angle B.

798
00:35:37,670 --> 00:35:38,550
So we can get...

799
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:43,800
What is the sum of angle A and angle C?

800
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:47,190
120 degrees, right?

801
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,110
Right.

802
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:52,630
From Angle A plus Angle C...

803
00:35:53,380 --> 00:35:59,680
♪ Walk on the same road a thousand times ♪

804
00:36:00,590 --> 00:36:07,150
♪ Run together and venture
to the distant mountains ♪

805
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:14,230
♪ We yearn for tomorrow
yet cling to yesterday ♪

806
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:20,570
♪ Leaves blown away by the wind ♪

807
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:29,010
♪ Spin and spin, spin a few circles
back to the starting point ♪

808
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:36,520
♪ Save and save, accumulate bitterness
to exchange for sweetness ♪

809
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:44,000
♪ When will we stand side by side again,
and when will we say goodbye? ♪

810
00:36:44,690 --> 00:36:51,090
♪ Like the swaying swing ♪

811
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:55,020
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

812
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:58,500
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

813
00:36:58,620 --> 00:37:02,450
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

814
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:08,530
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

815
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:13,020
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

816
00:37:13,050 --> 00:37:16,290
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

817
00:37:16,830 --> 00:37:20,120
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

818
00:37:20,580 --> 00:37:23,820
♪ The years are kind ♪

819
00:37:24,060 --> 00:37:27,470
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

820
00:37:27,710 --> 00:37:31,730
♪ Get through the coldest day ♪

821
00:37:33,070 --> 00:37:36,360
♪ Wait till the kapok blooms ♪

822
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:39,950
♪ When you come rushing back still ♪

823
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,000
♪ The young you ♪

824
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:48,200
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

825
00:37:48,220 --> 00:37:51,550
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

826
00:37:51,570 --> 00:37:55,300
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

827
00:37:55,320 --> 00:38:01,200
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

828
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:06,400
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

829
00:38:06,420 --> 00:38:09,440
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

830
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:12,120
[Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School]

831
00:38:09,770 --> 00:38:13,600
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

832
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:17,320
♪ There'll be sunshine through the years ♪

833
00:38:17,350 --> 00:38:20,560
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

834
00:38:20,590 --> 00:38:24,510
♪ Survive the coldest day ♪

